<TITLE> Diplomats from 22 countries visit storm zone, renew pledge to help </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BARISAL, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  Renewed assurances of support for cyclone survivors were made Wednesday after diplomats from 22 countries witnessed the devastation wrought by Sidr firsthand on a tour of cyclone-ravaged Patharghata in the south. In a press briefing in Barisal, on his way back to Dhaka, dean of the Diplomatic Corps and Turkish ambassador to Bangladesh Ferit Ergin said the international community was ready to help Sidr survivors. Brigadier general Rashiduzzaman gave an initial assessment of the damage and devastation in the southern districts. The diplomats arrived in Patharghata in two helicopters at about 11:15am. The envoys of the USA, the UK, France, Germany, the Netherlands, Denmark, Saudi Arabia, the UAE, Russia, Canada, Pakistan, Austria and India also took part in the visit to the storm-affected areas. bdnews2
